WHO: Biakato Mines region linked to recent Ebola cases

In its latest situation report on the 15-month-long Ebola outbreak in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), the World Health Organization (WHO) said that recent cases have been linked to the Biakato Mines health area, with 2 clusters of cases also reported in Mabalako and Beni.

