[3] Rapid response team
Date: Sat 16 Nov 2019
Source: Provinces 26rdc [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.provinces26rdc.net/rdc-ebola-lunion-africaine-va-installer-une-equipe-dintervention-rapide-pour-une-riposte-efficace-en-plus-de-fonds-qui-seront-collectes/


The African Union, through its technical body for prevention and fight against diseases (AFRICA CDC), will install a large team composed of experienced people in the fight against Ebola, which will have to intervene quickly and efficiently at each appearance of this epidemic in the DRC and in the Central African sub-region.

This team is part of several actions of the African Union in the response to the Ebola virus disease in the DRC.
Dr Jean-Jacques Muyembe Tamfum, head of the technical secretariat of the Multisectoral Committee for the Ebola Virus Disease Response (CMRE), 1st welcomed the announcement of an African Union Forum to be held on 2 Dec 2019 to reap the fund to strengthen the fight against Ebola.

He acknowledged the support of CDC Africa since the beginning of the 10th epidemic before announcing the establishment of a rapid response team in the response to Ebola. "CDC Afrique supports 60 people from the INRB who are involved in the response in the field. The director of CDC Africa has come to announce that the African Union wants to organize a money collection forum to further support the fight against Ebola. CDC Africa will install a great strong team that will stay here in the DRC using those who have the Ebola experience to be like a quick response team. In case of another epidemic in the DRC or in another country of the sub-region, they can intervene quickly "said Dr. Jean-Jacques Muyembe. For his part, Johnson Nkengasong, director of the African Center for Disease Prevention and Control (AFRICA CDC), said that the 2 Dec 2019 Forum is not late because it is a fundraiser that will continue and that will find ways to respond well to each epidemic.

"The Forum does not intervene late. It may be worth noting that during the outbreak in West Africa, the African Union convened a forum to support affected countries. In addition, we are at the 10th Ebola outbreak in the DRC. According to our estimates, there can be an 11th outbreak. So we do not want to be in a situation where we only react when there is an illness. We want to be in the situation of a prepared response. We believe that we have all the elements to make an effective response every time. Since you imagine if we reacted very early to the 10th epidemic, we would not be where we are today. We believe that these efforts to mobilize the fund must continue to support the response," he said.

Mr. Johnson Nkengasong welcomed the modernization of the DRC's National Institute for Biomedical Research (INRB) with donations from the Japanese Embassy in the DRC. This will help build the world's largest Ebola center.

