- Fri 15 Nov 2019. North Kivu (Goma) Vaccinator teams
[US AID; in French, machine trans., edited]
http://koma-ebola.info/goma-le-chef-du-quartier-de-kahembe-appelle-sa-population-a-recevoir-le-nouveau-vaccin-contre-ebola
[Byline: by Jeremie Soupou]

In an interview with Koma Ebola, Celestin Tulinavo called on the population to receive the vaccinator teams.

This Fri 15 Nov 2019, the 2nd day of the vaccination, several residents of Kahembe district came forward to be vaccinated. Confiding in KomaEbola, the head of this district, Celestin Tulinavo, who was the 1st to be vaccinated welcomed the involvement of the population.

"My family and I are vaccinated. The whole population of my neighborhood has appropriated the activity, prevention is better than cure. It is very important that everyone is vaccinated. I encourage everyone to be vaccinated. Even children a year or older must come for the vaccine. I have sensitized all my people for a long time. There is no resistance, "he said.

The vaccine is planning to vaccinate 50 000 people at Goma and could expand the activity to other parts of the province. According to the coordinator of the Ebola Virus Disease Response in the DRC, Professor Steve Ahuka, no one should be forced to receive the vaccine; only those who want it receive it by consent.

As a reminder, the 2nd Ebola-coined vaccine named Johnson & Johnson was introduced on Thu 14 Nov in the DRC from 2 health areas in the town of Goma.
